  Matrix multiplication benchmark — kostya/benchmarks.

  Generates two matrices with seed scaling, transposes B for cache-friendly
  access, then multiplies using triple-nested recursion. Uses floating-point
  arithmetic with Array<Decimal>:[Mutable] flat representation.

  Element (i,j) stored at index i*n + j.
  Generation: element(i,j) = seed / n / n * (i - j) * (i + j)
  |0.0.0.0|specified"
